    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi experts&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;When a user releasing purchase requisitions or purchase orders leaves the organization, it is necessary to create a new release strategy. This is because, if the same strategy is assigned to the new releaser, all already released documents automatically adopt the new user as the releaser.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Is there any way to set the releasing user in the already released documents? This would avoid the creation of new release strategies each time a new releaser enters.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thanks, Percy Rozas&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/management-of-release-strategies-for-user-changes/qaq-p/13971762"/>
    <published>2024-12-25T20:51:31.208000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
